  "title": "HTML encoding",
  "body": "Hello\r\n\r\nThere could be a way around this, but any HTML encoded values (e.g. &pound;) are displayed as the encoded value, rather than the symbol they should be displaying (£).\r\n\r\nTo explain I have a value in my template of {{ text }} and that attribute in algolia contains an encoded value, then the encoded value is output rather than the symbol\r\n\r\nIs there a way around this?\r\n\r\nThanks\r\nRyan\r\n\r\n",
